<br>
Immlazen I think you were right on target with your last two posts.  There is a distinct difference between whining and voicing serious concerns.  There are definitely people whining here, but frankly after investing so much time (if it didn't take so much bloody time to create a high level character) people wouldn't even think ttwice about starting new toon.<br>
<br>
There is some definite clear thinking here though.  Gauge you abilities against your peers in terms of desirability.  I'm on this Necro kick right now but I think it makes the point very well.  Look at these points about necros that I posted on another thread and then tell me why you'd bring a mage over a necro once PoP comes out:<br>
<br>
1. Pets in raids and in groups don't usually tank so their defense in those situations is irrelevant--damage is roughly equivalent against boss mobs.<br>
<br>
2. Their mana regen is the best in the game and getting better with PoP<br>
<br>
3. Pet heal is awesome (better than topor) and can be kept up indefinately against a mob since they can tap back health easily for canni'ing more mana. So their pets can tank effectively IF they so choose.<br>
<br>
4. Nuke is going to be less resistable being poison based(probably more aggro though) but then they have FD--death peace, and as much damage as our best nuke.  They get theirs at 61 we get ours at 65.<br>
<br>
5. They can heal, group heal, MW, twitch, FD for CR, Rez, Summon corpse--all very useful in groups and raids.<br>
<br>
6. Their short term damage will rival ours and their LT damage will blow it away when you factor DoTs.<br>
<br>
7. Not gonna even mention snare, fear, and mez--oops I did.<br>
<br>
8. We still have mod rod but all of us (well the great majority it seems) have come to the conclusion that if we are turned into twitch bitches what is the point of playing the class.<br>
<br>
Those are cold facts.  How can you just sit still and take that lying down.  I won't with over 120 days played on my mage.  Greater utility mitigates your damage potential or at least it should.  There must be a give and a take.  Right now I see take.  Once again our new summons help everyone not just us and don't gain us ground in the DPS dept, and our utility just got killed.  Just bot a mage and you have that taken care of.<br>
<br>
Nope I'm not going down easy on this one.  You're right though, thank God for alts and I will see how PoP works out and if everything stays about the same you will see a new necro on my server--along with my current alt druid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=magesthink>Magesthink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(10/11/02 9:12:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=135>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> your missing alot of information!</span><hr size=1> your missing alot of information!<br>
